<div id="pf2aca" class="pf w45 h233" data-page-no="2aca"><div class="pc pc2aca w45 h233"><div class="t m42e6 xb1 hc y153d ff3 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-(1 .1 </div><div class="t m44d xbc hc y1c39 ff3 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">CHRISTIAN FRIENDSHIP IS TESTED IN </div><div class="t me5f x58 hc y116a ff3 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SORROW, 1.055, AND IGNOMINY. PAUL KNEW </div><div class="t m415 x5a hc y10bd ff3 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THIS FRIENDSHIP IN Dr. LuKES FAITHFULNESS. </div><div class="t m1bf x0 he y2a01 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">age through Joseph. However, both Mary </div><div class="t m857 x0 he y2a0d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and Joseph were descended from David. </div><div class="t m611 x27 he y2b65 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m23ba x4a he y2b52 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How does Luke disclose our </div><div class="t m1af6 x0 he y2869 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lord&apos;s sympathetic attitude toward </div><div class="t mb81 x0 he y2107 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the poor, the lowly, and the outcast? </div><div class="t m753 x0 he y233f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 7:37, 38; 15:1; 17:12-14. </div><div class="t m2d5 x92 he y8f4 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Nora.—In His earthly mission, the Son </div><div class="t mf95 xb7 he y1c53 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of God became the Son of man, and the </div><div class="t m93 xb7 he y1068 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">unwearied Servant of humanity. </div><div class="t m7cb x27 he y13ba ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m896 x4a he y13ba ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How does this author stress the </div><div class="t m1465 xb7 he y2081 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">devotional nature of Christ&apos;s life and </div><div class="t m482 xb7 he y1db0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ministry? Luke 6:12. </div><div class="t m263 x92 he y116d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.—Luke presents three parables on </div><div class="t m1f1 xb7 he y1439 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">prayer not found in the other gospels: the </div><div class="t m375 xb7 he y